.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
LXD must be installed and initialized before using lxcmgr
.IP \(bu 2
Some operations may require root/sudo privileges
.IP \(bu 2
Container names must be unique within the LXD instance
.IP \(bu 2
Containers share the host kernel but are isolated via namespaces and cgroups
.IP \(bu 2
LXD can be installed via snap: sudo snap install lxd
.IP \(bu 2
After installation, run "lxcmgr init" or "lxd init" to setup
.IP \(bu 2
The script is accessible as both lxcmgr and lxdmgr
.IP \(bu 2
Desktop notifications can be disabled by setting LXDMGR_NOTIFY_ENABLED=no
.SH INSTALLATION
To install LXD and setup lxcmgr:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
# Install LXD (Ubuntu/Debian)
sudo apt install lxd

# Or install via snap (recommended)
sudo snap install lxd

# Add user to lxd group
sudo usermod -aG lxd $USER

# Re-login or run:
newgrp lxd

# Initialize LXD
lxcmgr init
.EE
.RE
.SH TROUBLESHOOTING
.TP
.B Permission Denied
Ensure your user is in the lxd group: sudo usermod -aG lxd $USER
.TP
.B LXD not initialized
Run "lxcmgr init" to setup LXD with default configuration
.TP
.B Network errors
Check LXD network configuration: lxc network list
.TP
.B Storage errors
Verify storage pool: lxc storage list
.TP
.B Container won't start
Check container configuration and logs: lxc info <name> --show-log
